mining the surface properties\nof supported trilayers and thicker films. In particular, we show that the\nstudied properties of the supported trilayers can be predicted from the lattice\nmismatch between the overlayer and the support. Namely, if the strain\ndependence of the corresponding quantities for pure strained surfaces is known,\nthe properties of strained supported trilayers can be reliably estimated. The\nobtained results can be used in the design of novel catalysts and predictions\nof the surface properties of supported ultrathin catalyst layers.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 27 Oct 2017 06:06:54 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 30 Nov 2017 08:15:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-01-31"}
