 to 16 microns) imager for use during the flybys, and\nmodified star tracker cameras to detect small (approx. 10 m) asteroids. The\nCASTAway spacecraft and payload have high levels of technology readiness and\nare designed to fit within the programmatic and cost caps for a European Space\nAgency medium class mission, whilst delivering a significant increase in\nknowledge of our Solar System.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 27 Oct 2017 15:10:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-10-10"}
